note 1on august 1, 2000, the corporation announced its intention to resume purchases of shares of its
common stock for the treasury both to offset shares issued in conjunction with company benefit plans and programs and to gradually reduce the number of shares outstanding. the announcement did not specify an amount or expiration date. the
corporation has continued to purchase shares since this announcement and to report purchased volumes in its quarterly earnings releases. in its most recent earnings release dated january31, 2012, the corporation stated that first quarter 2012
share purchases are continuing at a pace consistent with fourth quarter 2011 share reduction spending of $5billion. purchases may be made in both the open market and through negotiated transactions, and purchases may be increased, decreased or
discontinued at any time without prior notice.
